         <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1954-1968</unitdate>
         <abstract id="aspace_927c012b08e1c63c196001c667a76515">The collection consists of mimeographed copies of press reports from Czechoslovakian sources. The material was collected by David Korbel, an attorney who served as Secretary General of the Czechoslovak State Council (in exile) after the German occupation.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_898e1905647e14b8d59684f117d85c33">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_e5dbc254971f498213ad748205f92b32">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Czechoslovakian Press Clippings Collection (MS 1420). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_b6342a447915eacbdeeb904edd724b9d">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Transferred from the Slavic and East European Collection, Sterling Memorial Library, 1985.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <arrangement id="aspace_9ff164ef3cb634d34370b4c5d04c299f">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged in chronological order.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7d416245972c9534c2ad50fdeda42ac4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of mimeographed copies of press clippings and reports from Czechoslovakian sources. These materials document cultural, social, and political topics relating to Czechoslovakia from 1954 through 1968. There are no English translations for any of the items.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <custodhist id="aspace_a180bf80841f5a4607707e83458d71e7">
         <head>Custodial History</head>
         <p>The collection was compiled by David Korbel, an attorney who served as Secretary General of the Czechoslovak State Council (in exile) after the German occupation. The materials were transferred to the Manuscripts and Archives Department from the Slavic and East European Collection in 1985.</p>  
      </custodhist>
      <userestrict id="aspace_9b7460726e025bb062afe0f85328e04e">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
